%N A071877 Decimal expansion of the tenth (of 10) decimal selvage number; the n-th digit of a decimal selvage number, x, is equal to the tenths digit of n*x.
%C A071877 In other words, this constant satisfies x = Sum_{n>=0} ( floor(10*n*x) (mod 10) ) / 10^n.
%C A071877 The tenth selvage number is equal to the complement of the first selvage number (A071789): s_10 = 1 - s_1.
%H A071877 MathWorld, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/EquidistributedSequence.html">Equidistributed Sequence</a>
%F A071877 a(n) = floor[10*(n*x)] (Mod 10), where x = sum{k=1..inf} a(k)/10^k.
%F A071877 a(n) = 9 - A071789(n).
%e A071877 x=0.87653210876532109765421097654210986543109865431098...
%e A071877 a(7) = 1 since floor(10*(7*x)) (Mod 10) = 1.
